:::summary
The Renaissance ("rebirth") was a transformative cultural and intellectual movement that began in Italy in the 14th century and spread across Europe by the 16th century. It marked the transition from the medieval world to the modern era, characterized by a renewed interest in classical Greek and Roman learning, a celebration of human potential (*humanism*), revolutionary developments in art and architecture, and the beginnings of modern science. The Renaissance prepared the ground for both the Reformation and the Scientific Revolution.
